ZH: 我迷路了，没有指南针。
EN: I am lost, I don't have a compass.

ZH: 这本指南针告诉我们如何在大海上导航。
EN: This compass guide tells us how to navigate at sea.

ZH: 指南针指向北极。
EN: The compass points to the North Pole.

ZH: 我的指南针是个家庭传承的宝贝。
EN: My compass is a treasured heirloom.

ZH: 李明在野外遇到困难时，依靠指南针找到回家的方向。
EN: When Li Ming encountered difficulties in the wilderness, he relied on the compass to find his way home.

ZH: 这个指南针很精确，能在复杂的地形中提供准确的方向。
EN: This compass is very precise and can provide accurate directions in complex terrain.

ZH: 指南针是探险者们的必备工具之一。
EN: The compass is one of the essential tools for explorers.

ZH: 我在森林里遇到了一只迷路的小动物，用指南针帮它找到方向。
EN: I encountered a lost little animal in the forest and used the compass to help it find its way.

ZH: 你会使用指南针吗？
EN: Can you use a compass?

ZH: 我们需要一个指南针来确定我们的航向。
EN: We need a compass to determine our heading.

ZH: 指南针指向南方。
EN: The compass points south.

ZH: 请将指南针放在地图上，以确定我们的行进方向。
EN: Please place the compass on the map to determine our direction of travel.

ZH: 他的指南针失灵了，他不知道该往哪个方向走。
EN: His compass malfunctioned, and he didn't know which direction to go.

ZH: 指南针上的红色箭头指向北方。
EN: The red arrow on the compass points north.

ZH: 手表上有一个小指南针，方便旅行者确认方向。
EN: There is a small compass on the watch, which allows travelers to confirm the direction.

ZH: 指南针是导航的基础工具之一。
EN: The compass is one of the fundamental tools for navigation.

ZH: 我在山中走丢了，好在我有个指南针帮助我找回。
EN: I got lost in the mountains, luckily I had a compass to help me find my way back.

ZH: 他拿着指南针，朝着航海的目的地前行。
EN: He held the compass and headed towards the destination of the voyage.

ZH: 指南针在探险中起着非常重要的作用。
EN: The compass plays a vital role in exploration.

ZH: 张先生是这个地区最好的指南针制造商。
EN: Mr. Zhang is the best compass manufacturer in this area.
